<h2 id="detailed-analysis">🔍 Detailed Analysis</h2>

<!-- Area: Package Upgrades -->
<details id="area-packages">
  <summary>📦 Package Upgrades <span class="badge badge-teal">Tie — both inherit PF6 from main</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PatternFly 6 packages use the <code>^6.x</code> major version range. All <code>@patternfly/react-*</code> packages must be aligned.</p>

    <h4>Base branch state</h4>
    <p>The <code>main</code> branch already has PF6 packages:</p>
    <pre><code>@patternfly/patternfly: ^6.4.0
@patternfly/react-charts: ^8.4.0
@patternfly/react-core: ^6.4.0
@patternfly/react-icons: ^6.4.0
@patternfly/react-table: ^6.4.0
@patternfly/react-virtualized-extension: ^6.2.0</code></pre>

    <h4>Branch comparison</h4>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr><td>package.json diff</td><td>No changes</td><td>No changes</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Package alignment</td><td>Inherited ✓</td><td>Inherited ✓</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="evidence"><strong>Evidence:</strong> <code>git diff main..&lt;branch&gt; -- web/package.json</code> produces no output for either branch. All PF6 versions confirmed identical across all 3 branches.</p>
    <p><span class="badge badge-teal">Tie</span> — Neither branch needed to change packages; both correctly inherit PF6 versions from main.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Area: Modal Migration -->
<details id="area-modal">
  <summary>🪟 Modal Migration <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PF6 introduced a <strong>new Modal component</strong> (composable with <code>ModalHeader</code>, <code>ModalBody</code>, <code>ModalFooter</code>). The old Modal (with <code>title</code> prop, <code>ModalVariant</code> enum) was moved to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code>.</p>
    <p>The new Modal does <strong>not</strong> accept a <code>title</code> prop — titles are provided via the <code>&lt;ModalHeader&gt;</code> child component.</p>

    <h4>Base branch state (bug)</h4>
    <p>The <code>main</code> branch has a <strong>broken hybrid</strong>: imports from the new API path but uses the old <code>title</code> prop:</p>
    <pre><code class="diff-rm">import { Modal, ModalBody, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core'; // NEW API
// ...
&lt;Modal title="Custom time range" ...&gt;  // ← OLD API prop, NOT on new Modal
  &lt;ModalHeader title="Custom time range" /&gt;  // ← NEW API (correct)</code></pre>

    <h4>pf-codemods approach</h4>
    <p>Moves <code>Modal</code> and <code>ModalVariant</code> to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code>:</p>
    <pre><code><span class="diff-add">import { Modal, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated';</span>
<span class="diff-add">import { ModalBody } from '@patternfly/react-core';</span></code></pre>
    <p>This makes the old <code>title</code> prop work again, but uses the <strong>deprecated API</strong> instead of completing the migration to the new API. Also leaves a dead commented-out import.</p>

    <h4>semver/goose approach</h4>
    <p>Removes the <code>title</code> prop from <code>&lt;Modal&gt;</code>, keeping the new API import:</p>
    <pre><code><span class="diff-rm">-      title="Custom time range"</span></code></pre>
    <p>The <code>&lt;ModalHeader title="Custom time range"&gt;</code> already provides the title via the new API. This is the <strong>correct forward-looking fix</strong>.</p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Fixes the bug</td><td>✓ (via deprecated)</td><td>✓ (via new API)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Uses new Modal API</td><td>❌ Falls back to deprecated</td><td>✓</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Future maintenance cost</td><td>Higher (deprecated removal later)</td><td>Lower (already on new API)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Clean diff</td><td>Has dead commented import</td><td>Clean 1-line removal</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="evidence"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verified in PF6 type definitions: <code>node_modules/@patternfly/react-core/dist/esm/components/Modal/Modal.d.ts</code> has no <code>title</code> prop. The deprecated Modal at <code>dist/esm/deprecated/components/Modal/Modal.d.ts</code> does have <code>title</code>.</p>
    <p><span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span> — Uses the correct new Modal API instead of falling back to deprecated.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Area: PageSection -->
<details id="area-pagesection">
  <summary>📄 PageSection hasBodyWrapper <span class="badge badge-orange">Winner: pf-codemods</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, <code>PageSection</code> now includes a body wrapper <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> by default. Adding <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> preserves the PF5 behavior.</p>

    <h4>Base branch state</h4>
    <p>Three page components already have <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code>, but <code>e2e-tests-app.tsx</code> does not:</p>
    <pre><code>// Already migrated in main:
logs-detail-page.tsx: &lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;
logs-dev-page.tsx:    &lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;
logs-page.tsx:        &lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;

// NOT migrated:
e2e-tests-app.tsx:    &lt;PageSection&gt;  ← missing hasBodyWrapper</code></pre>

    <h4>Branch comparison</h4>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Branch</th><th>Fix applied</th></tr>
      <tr><td>pf-codemods</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Added hasBodyWrapper={false} to e2e-tests-app.tsx</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td>semver/goose</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">✗ Not addressed</span></td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="evidence"><strong>Evidence:</strong> <code>git diff main..pf-codemods-053126-0239 -- web/src/e2e-tests-app.tsx</code> shows <code>+&lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;</code>. The semver/goose diff shows no changes to this file.</p>
    <p><span class="badge badge-orange">Winner: pf-codemods</span> — This is the one migration area where pf-codemods addresses something semver/goose misses. However, <code>e2e-tests-app.tsx</code> is only used for end-to-end testing, not production code.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Area: CSS Token Migration -->
<details id="area-css-tokens">
  <summary>🎨 CSS Token / Variable Migration <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>All <code>--pf-v5-*</code> CSS custom properties have been <strong>completely removed</strong> from PF6. They are replaced by <code>--pf-v6-*</code> (for component-scoped vars) and <code>--pf-t--*</code> (for design tokens).</p>
    <p class="evidence"><strong>Verified:</strong> <code>grep -c "pf-v5" node_modules/@patternfly/patternfly/patternfly-charts.css</code> returns <strong>0</strong>. The variable <code>--pf-v5-chart-color-blue-300</code> does not exist in PF6. Only <code>--pf-v6-chart-color-blue-300</code> exists.</p>

    <h4>Base branch state</h4>
    <p><code>logs-histogram.tsx</code> uses two <code>pf-v5</code> CSS variables in inline styles for brush handles:</p>
    <pre><code>style={{ stroke: 'var(--pf-v5-chart-color-blue-300)', strokeDasharray: '5 3' }}
style={{ fill: 'var(--pf-v5-chart-color-blue-300)' }}</code></pre>
    <p>These resolve to <strong>nothing</strong> in PF6, causing invisible brush handles — a <strong>visual bug</strong>.</p>

    <h4>Branch comparison</h4>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Branch</th><th>Action</th><th>Result</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>pf-codemods</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">Not addressed</span></td>
        <td>Broken brush handles remain</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>semver/goose</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Changed to --pf-v6-chart-color-blue-300</span></td>
        <td>Brush handles render correctly</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <pre><code><span class="diff-rm">- style={{ stroke: 'var(--pf-v5-chart-color-blue-300)', ... }}</span>
<span class="diff-add">+ style={{ stroke: 'var(--pf-v6-chart-color-blue-300)', ... }}</span></code></pre>
    <p class="evidence"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Confirmed <code>--pf-v6-chart-color-blue-300: var(--pf-t--chart--color--blue--300)</code> exists in <code>node_modules/@patternfly/patternfly/patternfly-charts.css</code>. The pf-v5 variant does not.</p>
    <p><span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span> — Fixes a real visual bug. The pf-codemods branch leaves broken CSS variables.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Area: Select onSelect Types -->
<details id="area-select-types">
  <summary>🔀 Select onSelect Type Signatures <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>The PF6 <code>Select</code> component's <code>onSelect</code> callback signature changed:</p>
    <pre><code><span class="diff-rm">// PF5: value: string | number | undefined</span>
<span class="diff-add">// PF6: value?: SelectOptionProps['value']</span></code></pre>
    <p class="evidence"><strong>Verified:</strong> <code>node_modules/@patternfly/react-core/dist/esm/components/Select/Select.d.ts</code> declares <code>onSelect?: (event?, value?: SelectOptionProps['value']) =&gt; void</code>.</p>
    <p>Similarly, <code>Menu.onSelect</code> changed to <code>(event?, itemId?: MenuItemProps['itemId'])</code>.</p>

    <h4>Base branch state</h4>
    <p>Six files use the old <code>string | number | undefined</code> type for Select/Menu handlers.</p>

    <h4>Branch comparison</h4>
    <table>
      <tr><th>File</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
