<!-- Area: Popper onDocumentClick -->
<details id="area-popper">
  <summary>🖱️ Popper onDocumentClick Removal <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed</h4>
    <p>While <code>onDocumentClick</code> is still present in the PF6 <code>Popper</code> type definitions (v6.4.1), the semver/goose branch proactively replaces it with a manual <code>useEffect</code>-based click handler. This is a forward-compatibility improvement — the prop is on a deprecation trajectory and the manual approach is more explicit.</p>

    <h4>semver/goose implementation</h4>
    <pre><code><span class="diff-add">React.useEffect(() =&gt; {
  const onDocumentClick = (event: MouseEvent) =&gt; {
    if (inputRef.current !== event?.target &amp;&amp;
        !menuRef.current?.contains(event?.target as HTMLElement)) {
      closeMenu();
    }
  };
  if (isMenuOpen) {
    document.addEventListener('click', onDocumentClick);
  }
  return () =&gt; { document.removeEventListener('click', onDocumentClick); };
}, [isMenuOpen, closeMenu]);</span></code></pre>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Addressed</td><td>❌</td><td>✓</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Behavior preserved</td><td>—</td><td>✓ Same click-outside-to-close logic</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Future-proof</td><td>—</td><td>✓ No dependency on PF internal props</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="evidence"><strong>Note:</strong> The prop still exists in PF6 v6.4.1 type definitions, so the pf-codemods branch isn't broken for this. However, semver/goose's approach is more robust. Scored 4/4 for semver/goose, 0/4 for pf-codemods (proactive migration credit).</p>
  </div>
</details>

